values:
i must say, i am really enjoying life right now.







not.

whaaat the fuck.

i feel horrible.
i put [boy] through so much.
he is so great to me. he is.
i get jealous and insecure and i overreact.
i know i cant keep expecting him to take care of me. i know he has to take care of himself.
but i dont know how to take care of myself. i know i need help. but i soo dont want it. i dont
want to need help, i dont want to be happy. i dont want to have to start over from the beginning.

i told my friend. i told her stuff that was happening. she said
she didnt like that i would get better and she wouldnt. and i so
cannot believe that she would say that. that she wouldnt want
me to get better. because she cant. i know she cant, i know
her family life at home is bad. i know that. but to not want me 
to get better because she cant is really really bad. and i know 
that for sure.

I can tell people are getting annoyed of me.


And the people who aren't aren't associating with a certain person who is angry with me.


And it makes me so unconditionally sad to know that they listen to her and don't talk to me/ give me the cold shoulder based on things that this person is saying.







I'm so sad.

I wanted to bring in the goddamn chair on my own. I wanted to prove to myself that I could do it on my own. I did not ask for anyone's FUCKING HELP. I don't want your help. I want to do it by-my-fucking-self.


                                    I hate him I hate him I hate him so so sosososo much. I just want him to stop coming here. He can leave now and he just keeps coming back anyways and I hate him I hate him I hate him.



     She knows. She knows what he did and she doesn't even care.

                And I can't even put it because it sounds like so much less than it actually was.

                                      She has no idea how scared I was. I was so scared.


And now he talks to me and I just want him to shut up. I really do. Because that was one of the scariest moments of my life. And he is responsible and I hate him I hate him I hate him I don't want to go up to the cabin this summer. I really really don't.

Because that is where it happened and I have been putting off going there ever since it did and I really really just don't want to go up there.

i just want to cut my arms open and watch it bleed.
               i want to not have to worry about where a scar is going to be.

i want a motherfucking reason to try.
                       i want motivation
                               i want to energy to work at something.

              Tomorrow is our two months.

                                  And I have nothing for him.

                                               I have no fucking clue what to give him.

                                                            I want it to be something perfect.
My vagina is really really hurting and I cannot fathom why.

he is sore

i am tired




                       im falling behind again. this is a bad thing. i need to catch up with myself.
                          but the play really has been taking over my life recently.
                            ive been severly lacking free time
                             and all the free time ive had has been spent with him.

I have friends that make plans with their bestest's, plans that are for four years from now.
                          And I have never made plans like that.

                                Not with my bests, not with [[boyfriend]]. No one.



          And I think it is because I don't trust people, and because I'm so afraid of being let down when the plans don't happen. I don't want to open up to anyone, ever. The most I've ever opened up to anyone is to [[friend]]. And now she is switching schools. I am going to miss her more than anything ever. I'm crying at the thought of her leaving. She means a whole whole lot to me, she is an absolutely amazing person.



                         [[Boyfriend]].
                                He doesn't know how sad I am. He doesn't.
                                     Cutting is my one secret, and he knows it. He knew it right away.
                                        He won't tell me his. I don't mind that he won't tell me, really. I just want him to want to tell me.

                        Tomorrow I need to  really talk with him.
                             Talk, talk.
                                 Because I care about him and I want to feel like I can open up to him.


                                        And I want to feel like I don't have to ... fake it.
                                                          I want him to say the right things again.

So. Unbelievably. Stressed.

So stressed.


                            When they said it would be hell week I really didn't believe them. I mean, I knew we'd be at school until 10.30 every night, but I didn't think it would be so stressful.

     [[Set Director]] started freaking out at me. Because I couldn't find what she needed me to find, and I wasn't even the one who lost it. I was in the basement for a total of probably an hour looking for a cock gun and liquid nails. Both of which were backstage upstairs. She is the one who put me in the basement by myself with nails lying all over the place. What the fuck was I supposed to do?

                                         I kept thinking about it. And I don't want to think about that anymore. I really don't. I don't want to die anymore. I can't do anything while deceased. I don't want to keep thinking about dying. I don't want to keep having thoughts of suicide every time I see something that is sharp.

          [[Boyfriend]] deserves better than this. He deserves someone who is emotionally available. I wish I could give him all of me, I really do. Because if he had me then I wouldn't. I am not to be trusted alone with myself. But I'm so afraid of him breaking me. I'm so afraid.


                                                  I don't know why I can't tell him this.
                                 I have yet to cry in front of him. It's not that I don't trust him.
                                                                 It's not.
                                                                         I just want to pretend for him. I want to be better for him.
                                                        I want to be perfect for him.


                                                               I have a rash on my arm (disgusting, I know), and he saw it and I was like, "Yes, I know, it's gross." And he looked at me and said that there is nowhere on me that is gross.
       I don't know how he knows exactly what to say.



        I want to make him as happy as he makes me.

That is what I call it sometimes.
                         Because it never goes away.

                                   I was stupid to think that it would. It won't ever leave me.

     I can feel myself starting to slip back into the same dark lonely place that I was before. Back in 7th grade durring the whole ordeal with [[notfriend]]. I don't want to be in that frame of mind any longer. I don't want to at all.

           Last night at [[friend]]'s party I cut. At. Her. Party. I ended up crying a little. I didn't want to at all. I went just for her. I love her so much, and I wanted to pretend for her. I hated crying there. I hated it. Because it felt so selfish of me. The entire night was just a bust. And I feel so bad for cracking. But [[friend]] asked me, quietly, what was wrong. They had both asked me before if I was okay, but it was in front of everyone. She just asked me quietly what was wrong.

"I'm underwhelmed."

She asked if it was with [[boyfriend]]. I told her it had nothing to do with him. He is amazing. "I don't know what he sees in me." And then I just started crying and she hugged me and told me she sees what he sees in me, but I still have absolutely no idea. And it eats at me.

         I've been told my whole life that I'm not good enough. And that I need improvement, and someone liking me just the way I am, I don't see it. I don't understand how he can like me when I don't like me.




                       I'm crying at everything and it makes me feel unstable and vulnerable.

                                             And right now I just want him to hold me.

"Turn that light off!!!"
      "I am!!"

                      I am not.

                                            

I love the feeling of when he is driving and we are holding hands, and he squeezes my hand. Not to crush me or anything. A gentle, but firm squeeze. It's amazing.

        Today [[friend]] asked me what I think is holding me back from **v*ing him.

                                             I'm afraid he will hurt me. I don't think he will, nothing gives me that impression. I'm just scared to be vulnerable to him. I'm afraid that as he gets to know me better he won't like me anymore, he won't want me anymore. It makes me sad to admit that.

    It's not that I don't trust him. I do.
         But most of the things I tell him not because I want to, but because I feel like I should.



                                 Last Wednesday all I wanted was for him to hold me.

love

four letters. four huge, meaningful, bursting letters.
it is not a word to be thrown around.


i love people. i love my friends, i love my grandpa, i love my cousin. i love puppies.

i have never been in love. and i am so afraid of it.
                    so afraid.

i so badly dont want him to hurt me. so badly.

                 i realize i need to talk to him.
                        he has said it. mumbled and muttered it.
                              said he would rather die for me than live without me.
                                  and i would definately die for him. in a heartbeat.

                i love him as a person.
                                     as a boyfriend, i am more hesitant to use the word.

it's a huge word.

and it scares me to no limit.

Shut up and by the way I hate you.









I'm not sure that she even know that she is the reason that I cut.
                                         Every fucking time she says something to me.
                                         I get so pissed off at her that I just want to scream.
                               Instead of taking it out on her, though, I take it on on myself.
                                                                                                                            Typical me.
                                                                I will do anything to not accept help from others.
                                                                                             Even if they ask me a million times.

                                                         I think I just want someone to care enough to know that I really need the help that I wont accept.

Today had the potential to be a really excellent day.

                                 It failed miserably.

                                                                                   Today was one of the
                                                                                                worst
                                                                days I can ever remember experiencing.


Absolutely every little detail today enclosed me in it's darkness. Every single thing that could have gone badly, did. And I am left with no one to turn to. [[Boyfriend]] doesn't have to work tonight. Yesterday was our One Month. He brought me two roses. I think it is the sweetest thing. Yesterday was a good day.

I don't know where today went wrong. I don't. It makes me sick. I am in tears right now, with no desire to speak with anyone but him or [[friend]]. I can't call [[boyfriend]]. He isn't hanging out with me tonight because he had other things to do. I sound absolutely disgusting for even thinking this, but shouldn't he want to cheer me up? The prospect of seeing him tonight had me at least looking forward to something.

I don't know why I even bother getting my hopes up for anything anymore.

I could call [[friend]]. But she is so in love that it makes me insecure about my own relationship. She makes me question what I have, with how head-over-heels she is.



I want someone to do something thoughtful.


Instead I will lay by myself all night, listen to Matchbox Twenty, cut myself, cry, and wallow in self-pity.

I'm sad again.

I'm frustrated again.



I am in complete and utter alergy agony.

I miss [[boyfriend]].








I am underwhelmed and overwhelemed at the exact same time.

All-American Rejects.

Tomorrow.



I've been waiting so long for this, I'm nervous.



I'm ticked that it is an arena tour. That sucks majorly.





I'm still SUUUUUPER nervous.

I just saw a picture of a friend and I together. And I am fricking huge. I really am.

 

I don't want to be huge. I really don't.

 

My problem is that I am the kind of huge where people can still tell you that you aren't.

FUCK! Just now I realized that I am not wearing the sweatband that I always wear on my wrist, and all of my scars are visible. All of them. They aren't particularly light, either.

But no one has noticed, or they haven't cared.

He knows. 

He tried to take off my wristband. I wouldn't let him. He asked if it was because I love my wristband, or for something else.

I made him promise to not tell anyone, and to not look at me any differently. 
                                   [ [ I was so afraid that when he found out he would think that I am just another crazy sad kid that needs a new outlet. ] ]

He swore to both, and I showed him.





                                                   He told me that it was okay, that I am not the only one.

                                                                                 He also told me that he doesn't want me to be scared to show him anything. 
                                                         That he wants to really know me, not pretend to know me.                                   

                                                                   The best reaction there has ever been so far to anyone finding out.


And I feel so much better now that he knows.

So my dad doesn't like him and wouldn't even give him a chance and I'm upset at my dad right now because [[boy]] was super nice and my dad is just being completely unreasonable.


On the other hand, my mom loves him.

A couple of days ago when I told him how I go up to my cabin for three weeks durring summer, he said that he would miss me. And I know it'll suck a little but I'll still have fun.

But he said he would drive up to come visit me. And that would just be the funnest thing. Because the cabin is probably potentially one of the most romantic places and it would just be so much fun to have him up there. I know it would suck not being able to show him everything, but if he were to come up the week of the 4th of July, that is the most fun week.

Plus fireworks, and I'm sure we'll have worked out our kissing thing by then. ( All we really have to do is practice at it. )


                                    I just hope he doesn't change his mind, because I can just imagine the overall beauty of it.





                                           Also, there is a 5k walk for literacy coming up, but it is on a Saturday, and we have Tech on Saturdays, and I know I will end up doing the walk. But I don't know what he would do. I think I would rather have him do tech, just because it would be embarrassing walking with him, because I am definately not in shape and I don't need him reminded of my huge marshmallow body. I kinda do want him to go though, because it's always cool knowing that you helped out in something.




He really is cute.












                          I want to kiss him some more.

He kissed me last night after his orchestra concert. In my driveway at like 10 at night. So today after school we went to his house, only for like 1/2 hour, and we kissed a little there too.


It's not great, but I still like it.


I think it would be easier if I knew what I was doing.





He really is great.

I was curious to see whether he would want to hold my hand / cuddle at school.



He totally does.

He pretty much held my hand all day.



And after school we went over to his house and just cuddled on his couch. He didn't kiss me,but I kissed his cheek twice and he kissed my hand twice and so it's okay.

I was a little nervous, because I've never kissed a boy on the lips before. But the whole time, I wasn't really nervous anymore. Just... patient.


So I'm not scared. Cause I know that he will make it okay.



And I like him so much.

He finally did it.



HE DID IT.

And now we are a "thing."

So last night I went to [[friend]]'s party. The people there I've only know for a while, but are all very cool.



The point is, [[boy]] and I ended up cuddleing pretty much most of the night. And while he was walking me to my door, my stupid, stupid, STUPID neighbor was walking his dog and decided to call out to us and make it uncomfortable and that man just lost me my first kiss. NOT TO MENTION how my DAD opened the door as [[boy]] was SHAKING my HAND, per request of my dumbass neighbor. {{ I kinda turned the handshake into a game of thumbwar. }}








So it was excellent.

EXCELLENT.



superlative.

it really was just a lot of fun.

He still likes me.


He MUST still like me.




Today at lunch I got three hugs, and he was playing with and holding my hands, and had his arm around my shoulder, and was just being SUPER cuddley.

And he invited me to a party tonight so I really hope he'll ask me out at it.



*swoon*

I was planning on asking him out today. It didn't happen.


It didn't happen like three times.



But I'm thinking he may like me still, so that's good.








This is so nerve-wracking.

He's gotten more huggy.

 

And it's in a friendish way and I hate that. Because I want it to be in a more than friendish way. [[Friend]] said she really doesn't think he is going to ask me out. Cause I'm "a cool friend" and he doesn't want to mess that up. I want him to like me enough to be willing to take that chance. But I guess he doesn't.

Also, she said she's not even sure if he wants a girlfriend right now.  That's probably part of why he didn't ask me at Perkins. He's over me.


He's over me, he's over me, he's over me.




                                    And I am so not over him.



I wish I wish I wish I wish it all didn't just feel like this
I tried I tried I tried I tried to let you in
I want I want I want want want to not miss
I need I need I need you to hit this target








{{ I don't want everyone who said stuff about him to be right about him. }}













My heart doesn't feel good.

I got a hug today. He hugged me. cause I saw him in the hallway, and he just walked at me with his arms, like, outstretched. It was the best thing. And then at tech after school I had just gotten off the phone with [[brother]] and had an upset look on my face, and he noticed and PUT HIS ARM AROUND MY WAIST. It was one of the best things there ever was.

So I went over to his house today.



We played video games like the whole time, but it was fun.




But he still hasn't asked me out.


(We swapped phone numbers though.)



^_^

Now, I have thought about it. And when I think about things, I second guess everything.

And now I am thinking: What if he didn't ask me because he isn't sure if he wants to go out with me or not? What if he's changed his mind about me? What if [[friend]] has been lying about this the entire time?



I want him to want me so much. I want him to want to hold my hand.






I should not be left alone with myself for long periods of time.

So Perkins was fantastic. He was polite to the waitress, which I heard one time on a talkshow, you should always make sure of, because that is how he will treat you in 20-30 years. So that is pretty great. He did pay for me though, which I was kind of hoping he would, and kind of hoping he wouldn't. Cause if he wouldn't have, I would've been a little like "Yeah, he lets me pay for myself!" but also a little, "So does he not want to pay for me?" But he did pay. Which has me a little like, "I can pay for myself," but mostly, "He wanted to pay for me!!!" I can't stop smiling. Then we drove around for awhile, cause it was Saturday morning, so there was nothing really we could do. It was fun though, just driving with him. Then we went to tech. We got there at like 9ish, but [[friend]] didn't show up until roughly 11- 11:30. Awhile after she showed, her and I went to be secluded and do quiet work in a soundproofed area, and we started talking. Her: So do you wanna go out with him? Me: Duh. Her: I went up to him and I was like {suggestive tone} "How was breakfast?" and he said {monotone} "I didn't do it." As in, he was going to ask me out!!! !!!!!!!!! But he is a CHICKEN and didn't do it. >_<

We are going to Perkins alone. Alone, together. And I'm excited. And I'm fairly sure he doesn't know I'm excited, but god damn am I excited. [[Friend]] asked him. She is better friends with him than I am, and he said he likes me. He likes me. He likes me. He. Likes. Me. helikesmehelikesmehelikesmehelikesmehelikesme! He likes me. She told him that "she though I liked him too." Psh DUH. She knows I like him. But she didn't tell him. And she wasn't supposed to tell me he likes me, but she did. He likes me. And I really do like him. Sunday and Monday morning I was in a majorly sucky mood. And after that, all the rest of the week, I have been in an outrageously good mood. I can't stop smiling, I can't stop giggling- Today in math, math I was smiling. Before a chapter test that I hadn't studied at all for, I was smiling. And that was before I knew he liked me. (He likes me.) It's not as scary up here anymore, although I'm still a bit afraid of falling. I am starting to like it though. It's bright and warm and they have dish up here. I think I could live like this.

He drives me to and from school.

I really can't tell now if he likes me or not. But I want him to.


I want him to invite me to Perkins again. And again, and again, and again, and again. And I want him to like me.

I'm too into him. I'm not safe.



                             I don't want to feel this vulnerable.
                                This scares me.

I like him. [[Boy]] that I though for sure liked [[friend.]]

She said she liked him too, but just today she told me she didn't anymore and that she really think he likes me. She said if he asks me out, I have to say yes.


Uh, duh.




I'm scared, though. I'm scared at how happy I'm getting. Because if I get let down from this, it will be really deep. And I don't want to be that deep.


It's like, normally, I stay pretty much at rock bottom or a couple yards above it. Now, I don't even know where I am, but it is higher that normal and it is scary up here. I really don't want to fall.

I am such a fake. I am such a giant humungous fake.

I am talking to him. Right now. [[Boy]]. And I am getting that little knot in my stomach.
But I really don't want it to be there. It needs to go away.


I just want to want to be his friend and only that.

                             But I want more. And I feel really stupid for wanting more because he has been nothing but nice to me.
                                                       Ohhhhhhhhhhhhh. Oh boy.


He just said something on that little system known as AIM that made me inhale a little more sharply than I should have.





I hate how much I like him. I really really really do.

At this point I pretty much hate everyone.


I hate you, I hate your mother, your father, your brother, your sister, your cat, your best friend, your boyfriend, you girlfriend, your aunt's mother-in-law.




Everyone.

Guys Like That You're Fun
You're the type of girl guys brag about knowing That's because you're cool, funny, and laid back You're smart enough to know how to be one of the guys But flirty enough to know how to make them all want you
What Do Guys Like About You?

So I'm in another school "variety show." Recently I was in the Talent Show, and now I'm going to be in a thing that is going to raise money for Amnesty International.

Also, everyone is annoying me.



I think I annoy [boy]. But he's just so nice that he won't say anything. And the girl he was/is in love with, well now he's her friend, but with "benefits."  Which cut me pretty deep.

Also, I thing [boy 2] likes [friend]. I'm actually pretty sure of it. So that sucks.



And emo has been a recent topic of discussion between [2 friends] and myself. And along with that, cutting. And one of them knows I used to, but not that I still do. The other one is very ignorant. So they are both pretty brutal about it and it makes me cry.

I see how close I used to be with her and it really sucks cause now I'm not that close with anyone. And I know that's good, because part of the reason we stopped being friends was because we were both frustrated with each other and knew each other too well. I don't want to be that close with anyone again because I don't want the same ending result.

I had the absolute best dream of my life Wednesday night. I can't even write to explain it, I just know that nothing will ever be as good.


I guess I don't like anyone right now. There were two boys I was mildly into, but one of them is apparently religious, and the other one is on drugs. Maybe I'm too picky, but I don't want a bible hugger, and I dont want a pothead. I don't even care what he looks like anymore as long as he is a nice guy. I really just want someone I can relate to, that can give me a chance to like him before springing on me. And isn't a republican.


I'm so ill. I was absolutely out of it today and I can't even begin to describe how tired I am. My brain is asleep. My fingers just seem to keep moving. Type type type type type.


Just a nice, democrat, vegetarian, athiest, boy. Really.

That contest I entered? The one I worked supremely hard on.




Yeah, I lost.
So I guess I'm pretty sad right now

So life pretty much just sucks.

 

The guy I've been really into for like, I don't know, a month, well now I'm friend-esque with him, and since I give off a "trustworthy" vibe, and since I asked him who he liked, he told me.

 

He is in love with some blonde girl and has been for a YEAR AND A HALF. So I guess that's good for him.

Since I'm trying out this new thing where I'm nice to everyone and such, I helped convince him to ask out the girl. Which he is doing today.

I feel like such a fake. I mean, I'm glad for him that he is finally going to do something about it, and I really hope that she says yes and that they are happy and such, but I feel like a fake. Because I really wanted him to like me.

 

Eh.

 

Nothing I can do now, so whatever.

well ive been on the computer for over 12 hours and theres still absolutely no information on who won. the winners were sopposed to be notified today and there was absolutely nothing anywhere.

 

im really annoyed because i was going to do my science fair project today and i ended up the whole time online.

 

 

ugh i disgust myself.

So I'm going to do my homework. Like right now. I'm about to do it. It's just really hard for me to focus on it, I'm rarely in the right state of mind for it, and usually when I get there I have a disagreement with a parental unit and am immediately taken out of it. Right now I have to be downstairs because of the wireless internet being faulty and instead having to be plugged in. I'm in the wrong environment.

I know it seems like I'm just making excuses but whatever I am just really upset. I just started my period, my gifts from my parents are the most selfish things, I have a headache, and I'm commando right now because my maternal refuses to do the laundry. Have you ever been commando on your period? It is definately not reccommended. And I don't even have any fucking tampons, so I had to shove some toilet paper in my goddamn vagina, as I can't wear a pad, from the lack of clean underwear.

I don't want to do the work. I have to, but I know it's not enough. December, she wouldn't even bargain with me for grades. I really really really REALLY wanted to see my band in Wisconsin, which is only like 5 hours away, and she wouldn't even bargain with me for grades. I actually tried. I actually tried to get all As to shove it in her face and make her take me, but she wouldn't and I couldn't. That is why I don't want to do the work. I am so fucking afraid that it isn't going to be good enough. And even if I try the hardest I possibly can, and it's not the best that can be achieved, they don't even BELIEVE I tried, so I don't even get that sort of credit.

I really really don't want to be doing this at all. I am so thoroughly fed up with everyone. I told [[friend]] that I liked a boy and she was like, oh yeah I liked him last year and then tried to get me to hit on him FOR HER. Except she is dating a boy right now and it's most unfair that she can do that. And I told her I wouldn't even do anything, because she used to be like "in love" with him. And I told her she means more to me and she does, but I do not think she should let me let her get in the way. If our roles were reversed, I would most definately be telling her to fuck him or something. But that's just the kind of person I am. I am the person who is always there for everyone else, and when I ask someone to be there for me, they aren't. Because they have better things to do than listen to some pathetic little girl cry her heart out. And I always get replaced.

And to top it off, I have the hugest fucking pores you've ever seen in your life.

I absolutely do not like the winter. I don't like snow, I don't like cold, I don't like when snow gets on your shoes and the bottom of your pants and you go inside and take off your shoes, but the snow is still on your pants and it makes your ankles really cold, i don't like Forced Family Fun, I don't like being near my siblings, and I don't like the holidays.

They got me American Eagle mittens. From American Eagle. And I don't know what to say to them. Because they were from American Eagle, right, so they were definately expensive, and they were the kind that cut off the ends of the fingers, but have the little bit to cover them up again. But they're from American Eagle. And I know Ria knows that I don't like that store at. all. And Ria definately knows that. And she was the one who knew I wanted the kind of gloves that dont have finger tips. And the gloves are like, light pink and white and gray. And my jacket is like a dark green color. I didn't know what to say to them. So I was just like, yes, it's cool, yes, i like it, uh huh...

So now I am talking to [friend] and she doesn't even know I'm crying but it's okay because she is helping me without even knowing it.

Turns out the "contest" I entered that I worked extremely hard on is actually a "sweepstakes." Which means it doesn't matter how good or bad the entry was, because it is a completely random drawing. So it doesn't matter that I worked six hours a night for three consecutive nights to make it the best I could, because it could've been a picure of me in a band shirt with a santa hat on and i would've had the same chance.

 

I am very upset by this.
